edu.clarke.team2988.commands

Class ShootCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • Command
      • edu.clarke.team2988.commands.CommandBase
        • edu.clarke.team2988.commands.ShootCommand

  • public class ShootCommand
extends CommandBase
    This (inappropriately named) class is responsible for handling joystick trigger event to shoot the Frisbee by activating the ram which is controlled by the ShooterSubsystem.

    This command is instantiated within the OI (Operator Interface) class at startup and never terminates.

    Author:
    Micheal Dowling, Emily Snyder, Dennis Heflin
    See Also:
    Subsystem, CommandBase, OI
